The government says drought, political incitement and the availability of weapons from neighbouring Ethiopia are to blame for worsening insecurity in the border area. An overnight curfew has been introduced for the next month, and a disarmament exercise is due to begin. Cattle rustling has increased significantly in Marsabit, which is one of the areas worst affected by a drought across the Horn of Africa. Kenya's interior minister said police had intercepted a large number of weapons and ammunition smuggled from southern Ethiopia where federal forces are battling rebels from the Oromo Liberation Army. --BBC--